        "name": "commercial_linkage_fee_rate_usd_per_sqft",
        "parameter_id": "param-1-commercial-linkage-fee-rate-usd-per-sqft",
        "source_excerpt": "The San Jos\u00e9 City Council voted on September 1, 2020 to begin charging commercial developers fees to fund affordable housing. The Commercial Linkage Fee is a one-time impact fee that applies to new and existing Non-Residential Projects in San Jos\u00e9 that either add gross floor area or change the existing building use. The San Jos\u00e9 City Council voted on December 11, 2018 to pursue a nexus and a feasibility study on a potential commercial linkage fee in San Jos\u00e9. | Industrial/Research and Development (\u2265100,000 sq.ft.) | $3.58 - When paid in full prior to the Building Permit issuance, a 20% reducti [normalized=3.58 ; unit=usd_per_square_foot ; source_family=tavily_secondary_search]",
